Now we're ready to do some work

1. Go to 6-Gen-Grans

2. Write a program that will be executded like this:
   python3 gen-grams.py 2 Test

   2 can be 1,2,3,4 corresponding to uni, bi, tri, quad grams
     Test can be any folder in .../Corpora/Zipf/

   where 2 indicates bigrams and Test is the tokenized file to be worked on
3. The program does the following things:
   a. Reads in the file corresponding to Test.  This would 
      be .../Zipf/Output/uni/TestTok.txt
   b. Generates grams (bigrams in this case): the result is a list
      of tuples such that each tuple is one of the grams generated
   c. Count the grams and put them in a dictionary: Freq
      where each key is a gram represented as a tuple 
      and each value is its count
      Ex:
      File:  "hi there anya"
      becomes
      [("hi, there"), ("there", "anya")]
      becomes
      Freq:
      {
        ("hi", "there"): 1,
        ("there", "anya"): 1
      }
     d. Pickle the dictionary: Test.pkl and store it in 
